OL,6,FBut if you've been watching I'm a
OL,7,FCelebrity, you'll be aware of the kind
OL,8,Fof archaic compromises ITV has to make
OL,9,Fto stay within the rules.
OL,11,FITV is allowed 40 minutes of
OL,12,Fadvertising between 6pm and 11pm with
OL,13,Fno more than 12 minutes in each hour.
OL,15,FOn a typical weeknight, there are 4
OL,16,Fminutes of ads before 7pm with the
OL,17,Fremaining 36 minutes shared out between
OL,18,F7pm and the start of News at Ten.
OL,3,COfcom decision on TV advertising rules
OL,4,Cconsultation due soon
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G2/6
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,35903
SC,0003
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F359A1670850422
OL,6,FHowever the channel naturally wants to
OL,7,Fmake the best use of the limited
OL,8,Fadvertising time available.
OL,10,FI'm a Celebrity runs until around
OL,11,F10.30pm some evenings. So advertising
OL,12,Fis taken away from less lucrative slots
OL,13,Fso it can be slotted into the ratings
OL,14,Fjuggernaut.
OL,16,FFor instance, on Monday and Tuesday
OL,17,Flast week, there were no ad breaks
OL,18,Fbetween the start of the regional news
OL,19,Fat 6pm and Emmerdale at 7.30pm.
OL,3,COfcom decision on TV advertising rules
OL,4,Cconsultation due soon
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G3/6
