OL,6,FIt is important to look properly at
OL,7,Fwhether there are genuine economic
OL,8,Fbenefits to advertisers and
OL,9,Fbroadcasters from allowing more
OL,10,Fadvertising. It is possible they may
OL,11,Fconclude that the same amount of
OL,12,Fadvertising spending could simply be
OL,13,Fspread more thinly.
OL,15,FIt should also be clear that
OL,16,Fbroadcasters do not need to use their
OL,17,Fwhole allocation if they conclude that
OL,18,F"less is more" ` could rationed
OL,19,Fadvertising command a premium or boost
OL,20,Fratings?
OL,3,COfcom decision on TV advertising rules
OL,4,Cconsultation due soon
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G5/6
